---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Complete Electronics Recycling Guide - Step-by-Step Instructions"
  description="Comprehensive guide to recycling electronics safely and responsibly. Learn preparation steps, what to recycle, where to go, and environmental benefits."
>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Header Section -->
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Complete Electronics Recycling Guide</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Everything you need to know about recycling electronics safely, securely, and responsibly</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Table of Contents -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Table of Contents</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><a href="#preparation" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">‚Ä¢ Device Preparation</a></li>
            <li><a href="#what-to-recycle" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">‚Ä¢ What Can Be Recycled</a></li>
            <li><a href="#where-to-recycle" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">‚Ä¢ Where to Recycle</a></li>
            <li><a href="#data-security" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">‚Ä¢ Data Security</a></li>
          </ul>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><a href="#costs" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">‚Ä¢ Costs and Fees</a></li>
            <li><a href="#benefits" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">‚Ä¢ Environmental Benefits</a></li>
            <li><a href="#laws" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">‚Ä¢ Laws and Regulations</a></li>
            <li><a href="#faq" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">‚Ä¢ Frequently Asked Questions</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Device Preparation Section -->
      <section id="preparation" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Step 1: Prepare Your Devices</h2>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-green-600">‚úì Before You Start</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-600 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 mt-1">1</span>
                <span>Backup all important data to external storage or cloud services</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-600 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 mt-1">2</span>
                <span>Sign out of all accounts (email, cloud services, social media)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-600 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 mt-1">3</span>
                <span>Deauthorize devices from iTunes, Adobe, and other licensed software</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-600 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 mt-1">4</span>
                <span>Remove or transfer any active subscriptions tied to the device</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-blue-600">‚ö† Data Security Steps</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 mt-1">1</span>
                <span>Delete all personal files, photos, and documents</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 mt-1">2</span>
                <span>Clear browser history, saved passwords, and cookies</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 mt-1">3</span>
                <span>Perform factory reset or complete system wipe</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start">
                <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 rounded-full w-6 h-6 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3 mt-1">4</span>
                <span>Use data wiping software for sensitive information</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-700 mb-3">‚ö†Ô∏è Important Security Warning</h3>
          <p class="text-red-700">Simply deleting files or formatting a drive does NOT permanently remove data. Use specialized data wiping software or professional data destruction services for sensitive information. Many recycling centers offer certified data destruction services.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- What to Recycle Section -->
      <section id="what-to-recycle" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What Electronics Can Be Recycled?</h2>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-700 mb-4">‚úÖ Commonly Accepted</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-700">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Desktop computers</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Laptop computers</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Computer monitors</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Keyboards & mice</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Printers & scanners</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Smartphones & tablets</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Televisions (all types)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Gaming consoles</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Audio equipment</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Cables & cords</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-yellow-700 mb-4">‚ö†Ô∏è Special Handling</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-yellow-700">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Batteries (separate collection)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ CRT monitors/TVs (lead content)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Fluorescent bulbs</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Large appliances</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Medical devices</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Smoke detectors</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ UPS battery backups</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Industrial equipment</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-700 mb-4">‚ùå Not Accepted</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-700">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Light bulbs (non-fluorescent)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Household appliances</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Car batteries</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Hazardous chemicals</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Broken glass</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Non-electronic items</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Radioactive materials</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Explosives/ammunition</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-3">üí° Pro Tip: Check Before You Go</h3>
          <p class="text-blue-700">Different recycling centers accept different items. Always call ahead or check their website to confirm they accept your specific devices. Some items may require special appointments or have associated fees.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Where to Recycle Section -->
      <section id="where-to-recycle" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Where to Recycle Electronics</h2>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-purple-600">üè¢ Certified Recycling Centers</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Professional facilities with proper equipment and certifications for safe e-waste processing.</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Secure data destruction, environmental compliance, certificates provided</li>
                <li><strong>Cons:</strong> May charge fees, limited locations</li>
                <li><strong>Best For:</strong> Business equipment, sensitive data, bulk recycling</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-green-600">üè™ Retail Take-Back Programs</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Many electronics retailers offer free recycling for certain devices.</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li><strong>Examples:</strong> Best Buy, Staples, Apple, Dell</li>
                <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Free, convenient, often accept any brand</li>
                <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Limited device types, quantity restrictions</li>
                <li><strong>Best For:</strong> Small consumer electronics, batteries</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-blue-600">üèõÔ∏è Municipal Collection Events</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Local government-sponsored recycling events for residents.</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Free for residents, accepts most electronics</li>
                <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Limited dates, long wait times</li>
                <li><strong>Best For:</strong> Large items, annual cleanouts</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-orange-600">üè≠ Manufacturer Programs</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Device manufacturers often provide take-back services for their products.</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <li><strong>Examples:</strong> Apple Trade-In, Dell Reconnect, HP Planet Partners</li>
                <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Brand-specific expertise, may offer trade-in value</li>
                <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Limited to specific brands/models</li>
                <li><strong>Best For:</strong> Newer devices with potential value</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Environmental Benefits Section -->
      <section id="benefits" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Environmental Benefits of Electronics Recycling</h2>
        
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-green-50 to-blue-50 border rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-green-600">üåç Resource Conservation</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
                <li><strong>Metals Recovery:</strong> Gold, silver, copper, and rare earth elements can be extracted and reused</li>
                <li><strong>Energy Savings:</strong> Recycling metals uses 95% less energy than mining new materials</li>
                <li><strong>Reduced Mining:</strong> Every million recycled phones can recover 35,000 pounds of copper</li>
                <li><strong>Plastic Reuse:</strong> Plastics from electronics can become new products</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-blue-600">üõ°Ô∏è Pollution Prevention</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
                <li><strong>Toxic Materials:</strong> Prevents lead, mercury, and cadmium from entering landfills</li>
                <li><strong>Groundwater Protection:</strong> Stops heavy metals from leaching into soil and water</li>
                <li><strong>Air Quality:</strong> Reduces harmful emissions from improper disposal</li>
                <li><strong>Carbon Footprint:</strong> Lower greenhouse gas emissions than manufacturing new products</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">üìä By the Numbers</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-center">
            <div class="p-4 bg-green-50 rounded-lg">
              <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">50M+</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Tons of e-waste generated annually in the US</div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg">
              <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">20%</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Current recycling rate for electronics</div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 bg-purple-50 rounded-lg">
              <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-600">$60B</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Value of recoverable materials in global e-waste</div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 bg-orange-50 rounded-lg">
              <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-orange-600">1M</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Jobs supported by electronics recycling industry</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ Section -->
      <section id="faq" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Is electronics recycling free?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">It depends on the location and type of device. Many retailers and municipal programs offer free recycling for common items like phones and computers. Specialized items like CRT monitors or large TVs may have fees ranging from $10-50. Professional data destruction services typically cost $15-30 per device.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">How do I know if a recycler is legitimate?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Look for certifications like R2 (Responsible Recycling), e-Stewards, or NAID AAA. Legitimate recyclers should provide certificates of data destruction, maintain proper insurance, and be transparent about their processes. Avoid recyclers who offer unusually high payments or refuse to explain their methods.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Can I recycle broken or damaged electronics?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, most recycling centers accept broken electronics. However, severely damaged devices with exposed batteries or leaked chemicals may require special handling. Always inform the recycler about any damage when dropping off items.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">What happens to my electronics after recycling?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Devices are dismantled and sorted by material type. Metals are extracted for reuse, plastics are processed into new products, and hazardous materials are safely disposed of according to environmental regulations. Some functional components may be refurbished for resale.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Do I need to remove batteries before recycling?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Remove batteries when possible, as they often require separate recycling processes. However, don't disassemble devices if you're not comfortable doing so safely. Most recycling centers can handle devices with non-removable batteries.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Call to Action -->
      <section class="bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Recycle Responsibly?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6">Find certified electronics recycling centers near you and contribute to a healthier environment.</p>
        <a href="/" class="bg-white text-blue-600 px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">Find Recycling Centers</a>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout> 
